properties.title: Sticky Rice Travel Headquarters
properties.description: Our home base and the gateway to all your Sabah adventures, along with plenty of excellent day trips.

properties.title: Orou Sapulot
properties.description: Experience Murut hospitality, scale an 800 foot limestone outcrop, explore jungle caves, and sleep on hammocks at a riverside eco-camp.

properties.title: Gunung Mulu National Park
properties.description: Caves and cliffs! This UNESCO World Heritage site is known for its spectacular geology and landforms.

properties.title: Danum Valley  Conservation Area
properties.description: If you're visiting Borneo for the wildlife, Danum Valley is a must! Home to over 300 species of

properties.title: Bako National Park
properties.description: Sarawak's smallest national park is brimming with flora and fauna and wrapped in dramatic sea cliffs.

properties.title: Tabin Wildlife Reserve
properties.description: Sabah's largest wildlife reserve, a wildlife hotspot with over 9,000 hectares of unlogged primary forest.

properties.title: Kota Belud
properties.description: One of the most beautiful districts in Sabah, Kota Belud offers panoramic rice fields view with the backdrop of Mount Kinabalu and beautiful coastlines made of long stretches of uninterrupted beach and secluded coves.

properties.title: Crocker Range Park
properties.description: Choose from a range of programs including the Salt Trail expedition, Gunung Alab hike, Trusmadi Expedition, and a traditional Dusun village homestay.

properties.title: Kinabatangan Floodplains
properties.description: Consisting of five distinct habitats - waterlogged and dry forests, saline and freshwater swamps and limestone habitats - the lower Kinabatangan has one of the most diverse concentrations of wildlife in Borneo.

properties.title: Maliau Basin
properties.description: Known as "Sabah's Lost World", Maliau Basin was hidden from the rest of the world for centuries.

properties.title: Kuching
properties.description: The state capital of Sarawak, and a great jump-off for plenty of adventurous day trips.

properties.title: Mount Kinabalu National Park
properties.description: The heart and soul of Sabah. The highest mountain between the Himalayas and New Guinea, the mountain holds a distinctive position in terms of biodiversity of Southeast Asia.

properties.title: Sandakan & Sepilok
properties.description: Sandakan is Sabah's second largest city, and with the Sepilok Orangutan Rehabilitation Center, the Bornean Sun Bear Conservation Center, and the Rain Forest Discovery Center all close by, you can't miss it!

properties.title: Ulu Ai Experience
properties.description: Visit the Iban people and experience one of Sarawak's cultural gems.

properties.title: Kudat
properties.description: The Kudat Peninsula, the tip of Borneo, the heartland of Rungus culture! Enjoy long stretches of quiet beaches and quaint fishing villages.

properties.title: Semporna Archipelago
properties.description: A global center for marine biodiversity. Along with world class diving, the archipelago is full turquoise blue seas and white sand beaches.
